FBIS4-34404 "drlat118_o_94021" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 Colombia M-19 Leaders Urge Followers Not To Vote for Samper M-19 Leaders Urge Followers Not To Vote for Samper PA1806024094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 18 Jun 94 PA1806024094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours Newscast"] [Text] Presidential candidates Samper and Pastrana are touring Colombia hours before the election. M-19 [19 April Movement] leaders Otti Patino, Gloria Quinceno, Eduardo Chavez, and German Rojas have told their followers they should not vote for Ernesto Samper, because what the country wants is a government of unity, not a party government. [Begin Pastrana recording] I condemn any attempt to buy votes, no matter what. We want an open and clean election, and that is exactly for what we are going to fight. We are going to work to defeat the old policy, those who believe that by buying consciences and votes they can reach power. [end recording] Regarding the Liberal Party, Juan Diego Jaramillo expressed his support today for presidential candidate Ernesto Samper. Meanwhile, Samper said he is not worried about the tie the recent polls are indicating. [Begin Samper recording] Polls do not worry me. They indicate a tie, but if you compare these polls with other polls you will see there is an upward trend, and I believe that trend will benefit me during the 19 June election. [end recording]
